2,"Canal","Farakka Feeder","West Bengal",24.512222,88.058889,"To be updated","The Bhagirathi River is revered as the earthly form of Goddess Ganga and is deeply tied to King Bhagirath’s legend and Lord Shiva’s divine intervention. Flowing through sacred sites like Gangotri, Uttarkashi, Devprayag, and Haridwar, it inspires pilgrimage, ritual bathing, purification beliefs, festivals, and enduring spiritual devotion across generations today. <br><br> <a href='https://uttarakhandtriptrek.com/bhagirathi-river' target='_blank' style='color: #007bff; font-weight: bold;'>Read More</a>","To be updated","To be updated","images/placeholder.png"
3,"Canal","Mayurakshi","West Bengal",23.946389,87.524722,"Mayurakshi Reservoir Project began in 1951 and was fully completed in 1985. Initially planned to provide irrigation for Kharif and Boro cultivation, it later extended benefits to parts of Jharkhand and also supported Bakreshwar Thermal Power. Though not designed for flood control, it reduced the peak flood of 2000 significantly. <br><br> <a href='https://indiageomorph.org/uploads/pdf/JoIG-v2-(2013)-p037-045-Mukhopadhyay--Das---Channel-deranging-in-Mayurakshi-Kuya-interfluve.pdf' target='_blank' style='color: #007bff; font-weight: bold;'>Read More</a>","To be updated","To be updated","To be updated","images/mayurakshi.png"
