5,"Canal","Bagjola","West Bengal",22.618836,88.404295,"To be updated","Bagjola Canal appears as a sharply divided urban space where planned New Town modernity confronts informal settlement life. Within this landscape, squatter communities struggle against systemic neglect and displacement, highlighting the deep social inequalities embedded in the city’s evolving water infrastructure and spatial planning. <br><br> <a href='https://www.telegraphindia.com/west-bengal/calcutta/squatter-haven-called-bagjola-canal/cid/1787856' target='_blank' style='color: #007bff; font-weight: bold;'>Read More</a>","Bagjola Canal's urban landscape and socio-spatial dynamics. <br><br> <a href='https://ilkogretim-online.org/index.php/pub/article/download/2944/2871/5678' target='_blank' style='color: #007bff; font-weight: bold;'>Read More</a>","Bagjola Canal faces severe environmental threats from solid waste and untreated sewage, which clog the channel, degrade water quality, and increase the risk of infectious diseases. These issues, alongside industrial and domestic waste discharge, intensify flood vulnerability and pose serious public health risks to surrounding urban communities. <br><br> <a href='https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kolkata/file-affidavit-on-bagjola-canal-restoration-ngt/articleshow/107002358.cms' target='_blank' style='color: #007bff; font-weight: bold;'>Read More</a>","images/bagjola.png"
