12,"Canal","Beliaghata","West Bengal",22.566667,88.383333,"Historically, the Beliaghata Canal (Circular Canal) was vital for navigation and trade, connecting Kolkata with the Sundarbans and eastern Bengal. Developed during the British colonial era, it facilitated the movement of goods and was integrated into the city’s early infrastructure, though it later declined due to siltation and urbanization. <br><br> <a href='https://historyofbeliaghatacanal.blogspot.com/2007/04/history-of-beliaghata-canal-compiled-by.html' target='_blank' style='color: #007bff; font-weight: bold;'>Read More</a>","To be updated","To be updated","To be updated","images/beliaghata.png"
