15,"Lake","Rabindra Sarovar","West Bengal",22.512222,88.363611,"Historically, Rabindra Sarovar (formerly Dhakuria Lake) was excavated in the early 1920s by the Calcutta Improvement Trust to provide open space and manage urban drainage. Named after Rabindranath Tagore in 1958, it evolved from a marshy tract into a central public heritage site, reflecting Kolkata’s colonial-era urban planning.","To be updated","To be updated","To be updated","images/rabindra.png"
