17,"Lake","Senchal","West Bengal",26.983333,88.266667,"Historically, Senchal Lake in Darjeeling is one of the region’s oldest water reservoirs, established during the British colonial era (around 1910–1915) to supply drinking water to the town. Part of the Senchal Wildlife Sanctuary, it remains a critical heritage site reflecting early-20th-century hill-station infrastructure and conservation.","To be updated","To be updated","To be updated","images/senchal.png"
