51,"Canal","Damodor Canal System","West Bengal",23.238889,87.863611,"Historically, the Damodar Canal system emerged from the 19th-century colonial response to frequent flooding and water scarcity in the Damodar Valley. Integrated into the later post-Independence Damodar Valley Corporation (DVC) projects, it represents a long-term evolution of hydraulic engineering aimed at transforming Bengal’s 'River of Sorrows' into a managed resource. <br><br> <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Damodar_Valley_Corporation' target='_blank' style='color: #007bff; font-weight: bold;'>Read More</a>","To be updated","To be updated","To be updated","images/placeholder.png"
