53,"Canal","Kangsabati Canal System","West Bengal",22.956667,86.853056,"To be updated","Kangsabati River and its associated canal landscape hold cultural significance as the economic and environmental backbone of southwest Bengal. The river is integrated into regional folk life and agrarian traditions, where its seasonal flow and the Mukutmanipur dam area serve as vital sites of community heritage, recreation, and regional identity. <br><br> <a href='https://www.researchgate.net/publication/384446570_Water_and_Environment_of_Kangsabati_River' target='_blank' style='color: #007bff; font-weight: bold;'>Read More</a>","The Kangsabati Canal System is documented in hydraulic and environmental literature, which evaluates its performance and impact on regional agriculture. These technical narratives frame the infrastructure as a critical intervention in the Bengal landscape, linking modern engineering with the study of water-use efficiency and ecological sustainability. <br><br> <a href='https://www.researchgate.net/publication/239387760_Hydraulic_Modeling_of_Kangsabati_Main_Canal_for_Performance_Assessment' target='_blank' style='color: #007bff; font-weight: bold;'>Read More</a>","To be updated","images/placeholder.png"
